        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. In Israel, daily life under missile warnings and wartime restrictions Issued on: 05/03/2026 - 10:52 Share Israel's Homefront Command has announced it is easing restrictions that closed workplaces across the country. Businesses are able to reopen providing that there is a shelter nearby. Schools will remain closed. Daily life across the country remained upended, with civilians constantly having to flee to shelters, as FRANCE 24’s Simon Moritz reports. Iran hits Kurdish groups in Iraq as conflict widens 05/03/2026 US Senate backs Trump on Iran strikes, blocks bid to limit his war powers 05/03/2026 Pentagon releases footage of US strikes against Iran 05/03/2026 Middle East 'Notion that the Iranian Kurds could trust anything the Americans said would be pretty reckless' 05/03/2026 Middle East Confidence in Gulf countries as destinations and travel hubs 'has been fundamentally broken' 04/03/2026 Middle East 'Leaving leadership in the hands of temporary council could protect Khamenei successor' 04/03/2026 Death toll of strikes on Iran rises above 1,000, tens of thousands flee Tehran 04/03/2026 Middle East 'The fear for the Gulf countries is that the first client of the US would be Israel' 04/03/2026 Middle East US submarine torpedoed Iranian warship in Indian Ocean, Pentagon says 04/03/2026 Middle East"
