        "timestamp": 1772704288,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Iran hits Kurdish groups in Iraq as conflict widens Issued on: 05/03/2026 - 10:51 Share On Thursday, Tehran said it had hit Iraq-based Kurdish groups \"opposed to the revolution\", as reports said the United States was looking to arm Kurdish guerillas to infiltrate Iran. The conflict that began Saturday with US-Israeli strikes that killed Iran's supreme leader has spread across much of the region, sparking global economic pressure, energy disruptions and travel chaos. FRANCE 24's International Affairs Editor Kethevane Gorjestani tells us more. Video by: Kethevane GORJESTANI In Israel, daily life under missile warnings and wartime restrictions 05/03/2026 US Senate backs Trump on Iran strikes, blocks bid to limit his war powers 05/03/2026 Pentagon releases footage of US strikes against Iran 05/03/2026 Middle East 'Notion that the Iranian Kurds could trust anything the Americans said would be pretty reckless' 05/03/2026 Middle East Confidence in Gulf countries as destinations and travel hubs 'has been fundamentally broken' 04/03/2026 Middle East 'Leaving leadership in the hands of temporary council could protect Khamenei successor' 04/03/2026 Death toll of strikes on Iran rises above 1,000, tens of thousands flee Tehran 04/03/2026 Middle East 'The fear for the Gulf countries is that the first client of the US would be Israel' 04/03/2026 Middle East US submarine torpedoed Iranian warship in Indian Ocean, Pentagon says 04/03/2026 Middle East"
